# ABSTRACT
OPMap is a command-line based application that allows the user to
solve the Optimal Operator Placement Problem (OPP) for Data Stream Processing 
(DSP) Applications.

# AUTHOR
Giacomo Marciani is a MSc Computer Engineering student at University 'Tor Vergata' of Rome.
Author's email: giacomo.marciani@gmail.com


# REFERENCES
 * "Posizionamento Ottimo per Applicazioni di Data Stream Processing", 2015, G. Marciani
 

# UPDATES
SSP updates available at https://github.com/gmarciani/opmap


# TEST
The tests were run on a 2 GHz Intel i5 with 2GB of RAM, running Linux Ubuntu 14.04 
and Java 1.8.
Every JUnit-based test suite is available in package opmap.test.


